<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/magazine/4995624.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/magazine/4995624.stm" rel="nofollow">BBC News Magazine</a> <i>The Simpsons as philosophy</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> Mackie, J. L.. 1982. <i>The Miracle of Theism</i>, Oxford, pg. 203</li>
<li id="cite_note-autogenerated1-15">^ <a href="#cite_ref-autogenerated1_15-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-autogenerated1_15-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-autogenerated1_15-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="/w/index.php?title=Alan_H%C3%A1jek&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Alan Hájek (page does not exist)">Alan Hájek</a>, <a href="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/pascal-wager/notes.html#7" class="external text" title="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/pascal-wager/notes.html#7" rel="nofollow">Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> For example: Jeff Jordan, <i>Gambling on God: Essays on Pascal's Wager</i>, 1994, Rowman &amp; Littlefield.</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/w/index.php?title=Paul_Saka&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Paul Saka (page does not exist)">Paul Saka</a>, <a href="http://www.iep.utm.edu/p/pasc-wag.htm#SH3a" class="external text" title="http://www.iep.utm.edu/p/pasc-wag.htm#SH3a" rel="nofollow">The Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy - Pascal's Wager</a></li>
